{"key":"processedPost-4928343","value":{"id":4928343,"first":4926608,"last":4928386,"when":1131896202,"utime":"11/13/05 05:36 PM","content":"Correct.  Azurescens require a cold shock to fruit as do most other cold weather mushrooms.<br /><br />Cold shocking is a myth with cubensis and not required.  Cubes naturally grow in tropical climates and fruit very well in Florida and Texas in 80+ temperatures.<br /><br />Many growers think because they cold shocked their project, then got pins a few days later it was the cold that triggered pinning.  Fact is, they would have pinned anyway, perhaps sooner.<br />RR","title":"Re: Ice Blocks in the fruiting chamber. Will it work?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}